<br>
In NeuroML version 1.7, a simple mapping from MorphML and NetworkML to X3D was introduced.
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X3D">X3D</a> is a standardised language for 3D graphics
providing a XML-based follow up to VRML (Virtual Reality Modeling Language).
The mapping uses an XSL file to map the XML of a MorphML or NetworkML file to XML in X3D format.
To view the X3D, you will need a browser plugin, such as
<a href="http://www.octaga.com">Octaga</a> or <a href="http://www.mediamachines.com/downloads.php">Flux Player</a>.<br>
<br>        
